          public void writeExternal(ObjectOutput out)
                   throws IOException
          Note that only the relevant bytes are written, not the whole byte array.

          This means that when it is read back, start will always be 0. However, what is read back will "equal" the written value as defined by BytesSegment.equals(Object).

          Serial Data:
          int length followed by that number of bytes.
